      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "YOUR MAJESTY (9) has been good from similar draws in her two starts here since a spell, winning fresh before chasing a handy one in stronger company for a 4m fourth last start. Unbeaten third up so should be peaking and looks well placed. ALMIGHTY FEAR NZ (8) has been tackling stronger races of late and there has been merit in those efforts. Can measure up in this line-up. LEAF STRIDE NZ (10) was a big improver second-up when he came from a 40m handicap and raced three wide without cover but boxed on for a 2.5m second. Strikes at 50 per cent when third-up so can peak. SAN JUAN MOUNTAIN (3) draws well and must be considered after he came from much wider and finished runner-up here last week, beaten just a neck.",
